               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>This <ref source="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fetha_Nagast">Fetha
                     Nagast</ref> (fǝtḥa nägäśt, "Law of the Kings") was copied for mamher
                     (teacher) <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS000">Germā Giyorgis</persName> and his father
                     <persName role="patron" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS000">Ṣegē Mikā’ēl</persName> (ff. 144v, 147r) and was among the
                     trove that fell into the hands of the British at <origPlace>Magdala</origPlace>
                     in <origDate when="1868" calendar="Gregorian">1868</origDate>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="147r">1r-147r</locus>
                     <title>ፍትሐ ፡ ነገሥት</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ ፡ አብ… ንወጥን ፡ በረድኤተ ፡ እግዚአብሔር ፡ ወስነ ፡ ሠርሖቱ ፡ በጽሒፈ ፡
                        መቅድመ ፡ ጉባኤ ፡ ዘአስተጋብእዎ ፡ ሊቃውንት… እምድኅረ ፡ ሐልቀ ፡ ዓመተ ፡ ሰማዕተ ፡ ሰማዕታት ፡ ሶበ ፡ ረሰይዎ
                        ፡ ንጉሠ ፡ ፫፻፲ወ፰ ፡ ለቈስጠንጢኖስ ።</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Geez</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc material="parchment">
                        <extent> 147 ff., 4 flyleaves <dimensions type="leaf" unit="cm">
                           <height>34.5</height>
                           <width>26.7</width>
                        </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <collation>14 (f. iv) + 2–98 (f. 64) + 109 (f. 73) + 11–148 (f. 105) + 1510
                           (f. 115) + 16–198 (f. 147)</collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="3" writtenLines="28 37"> 3 columns, 28-37 lines per page.
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote script="Ethiopic" xml:id="h1">
                        <seg type="script">
                           Black ink.
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>                  
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">The phrase ‘pillar of faith <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS000">Tēwodros</persName>’ appears on <locus target="#147r">147r</locus> along with the names <persName key="person_f6581">Habta
                                 Giyorgis</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS000">Eḫeta Giyorgis</persName>. 
                        </item><item xml:id="e2">scribbles on f. <locus target="#1v">1v</locus></item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Leather over wooden boards with full blind decoration on both <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1850" calendar="Gregorian">late
                           eighteenth/early nineteenth century</origDate></decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
